{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TM4atgPn8s9r9U1LNPERSb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"use client\";\n2\t\n3\timport Autocomplete from \"@mui/material/Autocomplete\";\n4\timport TextField from \"@mui/material/TextField\";\n5\timport { useEffect, useState } from \"react\";\n6\t\n7\tinterface SchemaResponse {\n8\t  event_names: string[];\n9\t}\n10\t\n11\tinterface EventFilterBarProps {\n12\t  onFilterChange: (eventName: string | null) => void;\n13\t}\n14\t\n15\texport function EventFilterBar({\n16\t  onFilterChange,\n17\t}: EventFilterBarProps): React.JSX.Element {\n18\t  const [eventNames, setEventNames] = useState<string[]>([]);\n19\t\n20\t  useEffect(() => {\n21\t    fetch(\"/api/schema\")\n22\t      .then((res) => res.json() as Promise<SchemaResponse>)\n23\t      .then((data) => {\n24\t        setEventNames(data.event_names ?? []);\n25\t      })\n26\t      .catch(() => {\n27\t        // Leave list empty on error — filter still works as a text input\n28\t      });\n29\t  }, []);\n30\t\n31\t  return (\n32\t    <Autocomplete\n33\t      options={eventNames}\n34\t      onChange={(_, value) => onFilterChange(value)}\n35\t      renderInput={(params) => (\n36\t        <TextField {...params} label=\"Filter by event name\" size=\"small\" />\n37\t      )}\n38\t      sx={{ minWidth: 300 }}\n39\t    />\n40\t  );\n41\t}\n42\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19b45d90-1ce0-4130-bc08-6d66becae3e7","uuid":"bcccc36c-2590-47f1-8f7e-5186d2d33c43","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:44:41.759Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/explore/EventFilterBar.tsx","content":"\"use client\";\n\nimport Autocomplete from \"@mui/material/Autocomplete\";\nimport TextField from \"@mui/material/TextField\";\nimport { useEffect, useState } from \"react\";\n\ninterface SchemaResponse {\n  event_names: string[];\n}\n\ninterface EventFilterBarProps {\n  onFilterChange: (eventName: string | null) => void;\n}\n\nexport function EventFilterBar({\n  onFilterChange,\n}: EventFilterBarProps): React.JSX.Element {\n  const [eventNames, setEventNames] = useState<string[]>([]);\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    fetch(\"/api/schema\")\n      .then((res) => res.json() as Promise<SchemaResponse>)\n      .then((data) => {\n        setEventNames(data.event_names ?? []);\n      })\n      .catch(() => {\n        // Leave list empty on error — filter still works as a text input\n      });\n  }, []);\n\n  return (\n    <Autocomplete\n      options={eventNames}\n      onChange={(_, value) => onFilterChange(value)}\n      renderInput={(params) => (\n        <TextField {...params} label=\"Filter by event name\" size=\"small\" />\n      )}\n      sx={{ minWidth: 300 }}\n    />\n  );\n}\n","numLines":42,"startLine":1,"totalLines":42}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01GBZjcs2eqkfDU1zomoGnCC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me also look at the existing tsconfig and Next.js docs to understand what's there.\n\nNow, let me plan my implementation:\n\n1. Install `recharts` - it's not in package.json\n2. Create `src/components/trends/useTrends.ts` - Custom hook\n3. Create `src/components/trends/TrendsControls.tsx` - Controls component\n4. Create `src/components/TrendChart.tsx` - Chart component\n5. Modify `src/app/trends/page.tsx` - Full trends page\n\n\n6. Write tests for each component\n\nI'll write the tests first to clarify what each piece needs to do. The `useTrends` hook will manage the event name, measure type, and granularity state, while the controls component handles user input and the chart component renders the visualization. I'm outlining the `TrendChart` component with a chart type selector that switches between Line, Bar, Area, and Table visualizations using Recharts, plus a smart default that switches to Bar when there's only a single date bucket, and I need to set up the testing infrastructure to verify these components work correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1855,"cache_read_input_tokens":44144,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1855},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19b45d90-1ce0-4130-bc08-6d66becae3e7","uuid":"c6be96b1-46e1-43d3-82e6-8dd9025e25c6"}
