} label=\"Property\" />}`, the input element gets linked to the label automatically, so `getByLabelText(\"Property\")` should find it. For the `data-testid` on the Autocomplete itself, I can add it to the wrapper div instead of trying to pass it through inputProps. The test checks both `queryByLabelText(\"Property\")` and `queryByTestId(\"measure-property-select\")` when the property dropdown should be hidden, so I need to make sure both selectors work correctly. I need to update the MUI component props across several lines to use the newer API. I'm replacing `inputProps` with `slotProps` for Autocomplete and TextField components, converting `InputLabelProps` to use the slots pattern, and fixing the Stack alignment syntax to use `sx` instead of a direct prop. The `alignItems` prop needs to go in the `sx` object instead of being passed directly to Stack. For the TextField errors with `inputProps` and `InputLabelProps`, those also need to be moved into `sx` since they're not valid direct props in this version of MUI. Let me go through and fix all these prop placements across the file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3568,"cache_read_input_tokens":99971,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3568},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19b45d90-1ce0-4130-bc08-6d66becae3e7","uuid":"9e0ec5d3-99af-4ba6-b818-9bd826eeeaf5"}
